      "writtenOn": "2019-11-08T20:03:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We do need *some* version of google-chrome.\n\nIf I install all of the above packages except for google-chrome-stable, I get the following error when running the containerized tests:\n\n  Error: Failed to launch chrome!\n  /src/node_modules/puppeteer/.local-chromium/linux-706915/chrome-linux/chrome: error while loading shared libraries: libX11-xcb.so.1: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory\n\nThis is consistent with the comment here[1], which says the command above will install all the necessary libraries to make the Chromium version bundled with Puppeteer work.\n\n[1] https://github.com/GoogleChrome/puppeteer/blob/master/docs/troubleshooting.md#running-puppeteer-in-docker",
